headline_main: The Decade Tech Lost Its Way

abstract: His best-known book, “Frindle,” posed a question about the nature of words: What would happen if you called a pen a frindle?
snippet: His best-known book, “Frindle,” posed a question about the nature of words: What would happen if you called a pen a frindle?
lead_paragraph: Andrew Clements, who mined a brief teaching career in Illinois in writing two dozen books for young readers, most notably “Frindle,” which sold more than eight million copies, died on Nov. 28 at his home in West Baldwin, Maine. He was 70.

headline_main: The D.N.C. Chairman Knows No One Is Happy. Neither Is He.
headline_print_headline: Worst Job in Politics? Ask the D.N.C. Chief

abstract: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
snippet: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At the urging of Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey, eight Democratic presidential candidates, and Mr. Booker, have signed a letter urging Tom Perez, the Democratic National Committee chairman, to lower the thresholds to qualify for the party’s January and February debates.

abstract: A case against reputed Mafia members revealed their conversations when their boss was killed.
snippet: A case against reputed Mafia members revealed their conversations when their boss was killed.
lead_paragraph: On a quiet night in March, a mob leader was executed in New York City for the first time since 1985. The body of Francesco Cali, a reputed boss of the Gambino crime family, lay crumpled outside his Staten Island home, pierced by at least six bullets.

abstract: Workers at Loyola Marymount University are in a contract dispute, and all seven candidates who qualified for the debate said Friday that they would not cross a picket line to attend.
snippet: Workers at Loyola Marymount University are in a contract dispute, and all seven candidates who qualified for the debate said Friday that they would not cross a picket line to attend.
lead_paragraph: All of the Democratic presidential candidates who have qualified for next week’s primary debate are threatening to boycott it in response to a labor dispute between a food service company and workers at Loyola Marymount University, which is hosting the event.

headline_main: 2020 Democrats Threaten to Boycott Debate Over Labor Dispute

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson said the government now had “a powerful new mandate to get Brexit done,” a stance that goes against decades of greater economic integration.

headline_main: What the U.K. Election Result Means for Global Business

abstract: Britain’s currency has gained on the prospect that a Conservative victory will remove uncertainty about the break from the European Union.
snippet: Britain’s currency has gained on the prospect that a Conservative victory will remove uncertainty about the break from the European Union.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — When Britain voted in 2016 to leave the European Union, its currency plummeted on world markets, reflecting agitation over the economic and financial disruption that seemed to lie ahead.
